16 law enforcement officers have been arrested in connection to the death of a civilian in police custody. eNCA speaks to Independent Police Investigative Directorate Spokesperson, Lizzy Suping. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Sixteen law enforcement officers have been arrested in connection to the death of a civilian in police custody. The victim died at a Lenasia police station after allegedly being assaulted by Soweto Visible Policing officers and VSS security. READ: Police Brutality | 11 TMPD officers arrested The other three civilians were also arrested for violating the hard COVID-19 lockdown regulations back in April 2020. All suspects in the matter are out on bail after appearing before the Protea Magistrate’s Court last week. Watch the video above for more details on this story.